Refe : https://guides.github.com/introduction/git-handbook/

************** Handy Command ***************


# Commmand to clone/download a repository on GitHub.com to our machine
git clone https://github.com/me/repo.git

git status   : shows the status of changes as untracked, modified, or staged.

git branch   : shows the branches being worked on locally.

git pull     : (equal to fecth and merge )updates the local line of development with updates from its remote counterpart. 
				Developers use this command if a teammate has made commits to a branch on a remote, and they would like to reflect 
				those changes in their local environment.
				

git checkout my-branch  : switch to that branch (line of development)

// after above comman your current branch is my-branch
// Now comman to merge master into current branch.

git merge master // this will merge master to your current and you can commit and push this to repo

// command to stash you code.

git stash